'''''Star Wars Insider'' 66''' is the sixty-sixth issue of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine. It was released to newsstands on [[March 4]], [[2003]].

==Contents==
===Departments===
*From the Editor's Desk
*[[Rebel Rumblings]]
*[[Star News]] {{C|by [[Benjamin Harper]]}}
*[[The Jawa Trader|Jawa Trader]]
*[[Behind the Magic]] &mdash; Kaminoan to My House {{C|by [[Rob Coleman]]}}
*[[HoloNet News (Insider)|HoloNet News]] {{C|by [[Pablo Hidalgo]]}}
**[[Republic HoloNet News Core Edition 14:3:22]]
**[[CIS Shadowfeed Dispatch 14:3:10 Edition]]
*[[Gamescape]]
**Walk Like a Trandoshan {{C|by [[Michael Mikaelian]]}}
**That's No Moon! {{C|by [[W. Haden Blackman]]}}
**''Star Wars'' Galaxies Update {{C|by Haden Blackman}}
*[[Bookshelf]] &mdash; [[Tatooine Ghost|Twin Suns for Twin Eras]] {{C|by [[Jason Fry]]}}
*[[Comics Link]] &mdash; Biggs Darklighter {{C|by [[Daniel Wallace]]}}
*[[Set Piece]]: Jedi Council Chamber {{C|by [[Chris Trevas]]}}
*[[Scouting the Galaxy]] &mdash; All Answers, All The Time {{C|by [[Stephen J. Sansweet|Steve Sansweet]]}}
*[[Crossword (department)|Crossword]] &mdash; Constant Collaborators {{C|by [[Michael Selinker]]}}
*[[Star Wars Q&A|''Star Wars'' Q&A]] {{C|by Pablo Hidalgo}}
*[[The Last Page]] {{C|by [[Tony Moseley]]}}

===Features===
*"[[Prequel Update]]" {{C|by [[Dave Gross]]}}
*:<small>[[Rick McCallum]] reports from Australia about preparing to build the first sets for [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|Episode III]].</small>
*"[[Inside Attack of the Clones|Inside ''Attack of the Clones'']]" {{C|by [[David West Reynolds (real person)|David West Reynolds]]}}
*:<small>A guided tour of the [[Geonosian/Legends|Geonosian]] war room deep beneath the red [[Planet/Legends|planet's]] surface.</small>
*"[[War Factories: Inside Kamino and Geonosis]]" {{C|by [[Daniel Wallace]]}}
*:<small>[[Kamino/Legends|Kamino]] and [[Geonosis/Legends|Geonosis]] look as different as two worlds can, and so do the beings who live on them, yet both serve the same ultimate purpose: war.</small>
*"[[Novel Approach]]" {{C|by [[Rich Handley]]}}
*:<small>The rich tapestry of ''[[Star Wars]]'' lore is more than a few movies can contain.</small>
*"[[Elusion Illusion]]" {{C|by [[Michael A. Stackpole]]}}
*:<small>[[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]] [[Aayla Secura/Legends|Aayla Secura]] wonders why [[Jedi Master/Legends|Master]] [[Mace Windu/Legends|Mace Windu]] chose her for such a crucial mission, but soon she learns she might be all that stands between [[Corellia/Legends|Corellia]] and the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Separatists]].</small>
*"[[Who's Who: Imperial Grand Admirals]]" {{C|by Daniel Wallace and [[Abel G. Peña]].}}
*:<small>A look inside the minds of thirteen of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Empire's]] most ingenious military leaders.</small>
*"[[What You Don't See: The Invisible Effects of The Phantom Menace|What You Don't See: The Invisible Effects of ''The Phantom Menace'']]" {{C|by [[Ron Magid]].}}
*:<small>[[George Lucas]] settles only for the best, even if he has to get it from three different takes.</small>
*"[[Star Wars at the Movies|''Star Wars'' at the Movies]]" {{C|by [[Francis K. Lalumiere]]}}
*:<small>Filmmakers have been putting a little ''Star Wars'' in their own movies for nearly twenty-five years.</small>
*"[[Insider Interview]]: C-3PO" {{C|by [[Kevin Rubio]]}}
*:<small>Kevin had no idea how hard it would be to get an interview with [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]].</small>

